The course provides an overview of physiotherapy, its various fields, job opportunities, and the rehabilitation and health care system in Estonia. It offers initial information on the use of the International Classification of Functioning, Disability, and Health (ICF) and the work of professional organizations in the field in Estonia and around the world. As part of the course, various institutions providing physiotherapy services will be visited to gain a deeper understanding of the daily work of a physiotherapist. The course also covers current professional requirements (laws), data protection, and ethical principles related to the field.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide an overview of physiotherapy, its various fields, employment opportunities, and the rehabilitation and health care system in Estonia. Familiarize with the International Classification of Functioning, Disability, and Health.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student: - Describes the essence of physiotherapy and rehabilitation system in Estonia. - Knows and understands the ethical requirements and key principles related to personal data protection in physiotherapy, as well as comprehends the principles of protecting personal data within the framework of healthcare services. - Analyzes the necessity of teamwork in the rehabilitation system. - Describes the roles of different team members in the rehabilitation team. - Knows the structure and basis of the International Classification of Functioning, Disability, and Health (ICF) used in the healthcare system. - Is able to use databases for searching scientific physiotherapy literature, summarize articles, and present essential information to listeners.
